org.asoem.greyfish.utils.collect

Interface Product2<E1,E2>

  • Type Parameters:
    E1 - the type of the first value
    E2 - the type of the second value
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Point2D, RecombinationProduct<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractPoint2D, ImmutablePoint2D, MutablePoint2D, Tuple2

    public interface Product2<E1,E2>
    A generic interface for objects which encapsulate a pair of values.

    Don't overuse this interface! For a matter of readability you should consider to write your own pair class if you don't use any utility function associated with it (see Products) or add methods with names of a defined meaning to the implementation which delegate to the generic accessor functions.
